[asy]
import three;

size(180);
currentprojection = perspective(6,3,2);

triple A, B, C, D, O;

A = (0,0,0);
B = (1,0,0);
C = (0,1,0);
D = (0,0,1);
O = (B + C)/2;

draw(B--C--D--cycle);
draw(A--B);
draw(A--C);
draw(A--D);
draw(D--O,dashed);

label("$A$", A, SW);
label("$B$", B, S);
label("$C$", C, W);
label("$D$", D, N);
label("$O$", O, S);
[/asy]

Since $\angle ADB = \angle ADC = \angle BDC = 90^\circ,$ $DO$ is the altitude from $D$ to $\triangle ABC.$  Also, $DO$ is the median to hypotenuse $BC$ of right triangle $BDC,$ so $DO = BO = CO.$

Then
\[\cos \angle ACB = \frac{CO}{BC} = \frac{DO}{BC}.\]From right triangle $ADO,$
\[\sin \angle CAD = \frac{DO}{AD} = x,\]so $DO = x \cdot AD.$

From right triangle $BDO,$
\[\sin \angle CBD = \frac{DO}{BD} = y,\]so $DO = y \cdot BD.$

Hence, $x \cdot AD = y \cdot BD,$ so
\[\frac{AD}{BD} = \frac{y}{x}.\]Then from right triangle $ABD,$
\[\frac{DO}{BC} = \frac{DO/BD}{BC/BD} = \frac{y}{x} \cdot \frac{AD}{BD} = \frac{y}{x} \cdot \frac{y}{x} = \boxed{\frac{y^2}{x^2}}.\]

